---
name: form-header and form-footer
description: |
  The form header and footer components can be used to put some distance between the form components
  and their setup and submission content.
order: 2
tips: |
  - These layout features are most useful in larger forms. If you have a small form like a login they're optional.
links:
    Long form: /demos/forms/long.html
    Account signup: /demos/forms/accounts.html
---

<form class="mzp-c-form">
  <div class="mzp-c-form-header">
      <h2 class="mzp-c-form-heading">Heading</h2>
      <p>The heading and this paragraph are inside a form-header.</p>
  </div>
  <fieldset class="mzp-c-field-set">
    {{#embed "patterns.molecules.forms.fields.input" id="id_name" name="name" type="text"}}
      {{#content "label"}}Label{{/content}}
    {{/embed}}
    {{#embed "patterns.molecules.forms.fields.input" id="id_user_email" name="user_email" type="text"  info="true" }}
      {{#content "label"}}Label{{/content}}
      {{#content "info"}}Supplementary information about the form fields can be included in a field-info.{{/content}}
    {{/embed}}
  </fieldset>
  <div class="mzp-c-form-footer">
    <p>This paragraph and the elements below are in a form-footer</p>
    <button class="mzp-c-button">Button</button>
    <p class="mzp-c-form-info mzp-t-xs">The button container component is optional - use it for button alignment options if you need them.</p>
  <div>
</form>
